          "process_md": "> ***Application Process for Student:***\n\n**Document Preparation:**\n\n- Ensure all required documents are ready, including Aadhaar, caste certificate, income certificate (if applicable), and Aadhaar-linked bank account details.\n\n**Submission to School:**\n\n- Submit the required documents and information to the school principal for entry into the e-Kalyan portal.\n\n**Aadhaar Authentication:**\n\n- Ensure Aadhaar authentication is completed to generate a unique ID for the application.\n\n<br>\n\n> ***Application Process for Schools (Principal/INO Role):***\n\n**Login Setup:**\n- Principals or headmasters (Institute Nodal Officers) register schools using their UDISE code on the [e-Kalyan portal](https://ekalyan.cgg.gov.in/Login.do).**Student Registration:**\n- The school head enters eligible students’ details (name, DOB, Aadhaar).\n- New students must be registered immediately upon enrollment.\n**Aadhaar Authentication:**\n- A unique ID is generated post-verification and is valid for subsequent years.\n**Approval Workflow:**\n- Applications are verified by District Nodal Officers (DNOs) and forwarded to the District Level Approval Committee.\n- Approved applications are sent to the State Nodal Officer (SNO) for integration and payment processing.\n**Scholarship Disbursement:**\n- Payments are made through the Aadhaar Payment Bridge System (APBS) or PFMS/NACH for non-linked accounts.\n"
        }
